result.execSummary:
The defendant Deitrik Jerome Lloyd Ellis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License(3rd+ w/in3Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged or terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of any restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  Must pay all costs of the action during the term of probation.

Must seek and maintain full-time employment or a combination of employment and education to get HSED or GED whichever is satisfactory to your probation agent.  Defendant  must not leave or change employment without prior approval of your probation agent.  A combination of employment and education will be left up to your agent.
Must not operate a motor vehicle until licensed and insured.  Must work towards getting licensed and if defendant becomes licensed he must get permission of agent to drive.

The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Must participate in CGIP.  Must provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge.

16CM125 & 16TR2816:  Defendant appears in person with counsel SPD Travis Satorius.  Gerald Fox appears for the State.  Court makes note that the plea questionnaire does not have the correct charge. The correct charge in 16CM125 is No Valid D.L. 3rd.  Defendant understands that charge and penalties, enters plea of No Contest.  Court reviews the correct elements with the defendant.  Plea/waiver of rights colloquy performed with defendant. Defendant admits to the prior convictions.  Defense stipulates to the factual basis in the complaint.  Court finds he FVKI enters his plea and waives his rights and finds him guilty.  16TR2816 is dismissed and read-in.  DA Fox recommends probation for 1 year with conditions:  Must not operate a motor vehicle until licensed and insured.  Must undergo a risk & needs assessment and comply with any recommendations and sign release.  Must participate in CGIP.  If defendant becomes licensed he must get permission of agent to drive.  Must provide a DNA sample.  DA Fox states he is eligible to get license he just doesn't do it.  Attorney Satorius agrees with probation recommendation.

Court adopts joint recommendation, withholds sentence and places on 1 year probation with the requested conditions plus:  Must work towards getting your license; HSED or GED or seek and maintain employment or combination of both - will be left up to agent.  Mut pay costs of action during term of probation .  Report to probation today.
